[The anti-rabies vaccine should ALWAYS be given if you think you have been bitten, scratched contaminated with bloody, saliva of a suspected rabid animal in ALL cases. This man was bitten in September, and did not immediately seek treatment. His prospects are almost nil now.

Vampire bat rabies is common throughout Brazil and is why domestic and livestock, especially valuable animals, must be vaccinated. This farmer has only a small chance of survival. - Mod.MHJ

